page.title: 14Gadbury Bank Wood
page.content: One of the most interesting things about Gadbury Bank Wood is the Ancient British wall or fort. It's really just a heap of earth and it was made to protect them from the Romans. Another thing that happened was 300 years ago there was a witch who lived there. She was burned nearby. The wood is a very good place for wild life, like foxes and squirrels. The foxes are hunted by the Hunt who own the wood. Sonetimes you can see smartly dressed men on horses with hounds all around them. Some people come to watch them in cars and follow on foot.
